See also m40 Card. A laurel wreath is a wreath made of branches and leaves of the laurel (latin laurus). The laurel wreath is a symbol and an insignia for a special honor or distinction, for a victory (eg. for killing sheeps or even innocent children) or a special success. So to say the special super-duper superman hero
To compensate low self-esteem (object fixation) with this once-received laurel wreath. About as Intelligent as using always the one and the same One-Time-Pad.

In the Middle Ages a fool or a Tor (german: töricht = foolish) was the person, who entertained the royal household and was dressed mostly strange but funny. The term "fool" also refers to persons who are very immature, stupid, clumsy, biased, prejudiced, ignorant. I guess "ignorant" was inserted later. The fool is normally not ignorant and if the king has a black heart it would be even dangerous to tell himwhat many others think directly in his ****** face.

Kings often do not want to look in the mirror because they know normally that they are fat, hairy and ignorant. The fool tries to show the king his own stupidity without being killed (jester's licence) by the king ( = Satan )
